The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 23: The Reserve Bank (RBI) 

 has announced revised guidelines governing banks exposure 

 to venture capital funds (VCFs), which include ceiling on 

 paid-up capital and investments by banks in VCFs. All exposures 

 to VCFs will be deemed to be on a par with equity and will 

 be reckoned for compliance with the capital market exposure 

 ceilings.

 Kuala Lumpur, Aug. 23: Japan has proposed 

 the creation of a 16-nation pan-Asian free trade area, including 

 India, with economic activity worth $9 trillion. However, 

 Asean, which has approved the idea, asked Tokyo to conclude 

 the Asean-Japan trade pact first. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 23: The Lok Sabha today approved a bill to give more flexibility to boards of directors and improving corporate governance standards in public sector banks. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 23: The legal battle for control of Haldia Petrochemicals took a new twist today when The Chatterjee Group contended before the company law board that 15.5 crore shares of the company were unaccounted for and beyond its paid-up capital.

 Calcutta, Aug. 23: Rajender S. Lodha 

 has filed an appeal in Calcutta High Court, challenging 

 an order of the company law board that held transfer of 

 Priyamvada Birlas shares in his name as wrongful and asked 

 it to be restored in the name of the original owner.




